						               													<description>A diorama-style powerful game board!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Combines elements of standard memory game and traditional collect-and-win family games in a wonderful world of My Neighbor Totoro by Studio Ghibli.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game you will play as one of four small Totoros. &amp;#10;On your turn you will roll the dice to move around big camphor tree and then:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-uncover as many matching memo cards as possible to get more acorns or get suprised upon uncovering disadvantage memo card&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-encounter middle Totoro and move your Makkuro Kurosuke figure to the next level of the tree (this will also give you more acorns)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-perform special actions (only on specific fields): redraw or cards uncovering&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game finishes when any players Makkuro Kurosuke reaches the top of the camphor tree.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Goal:&amp;#10;To win the game collect the most acorns of all players until any player reaches top of the camphor tree!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sounds simple, but surely satisfies with uniquely modified memo-game mechanics and surpising bonuses or disadvantages, which may cause sudden twist in overall outcome of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Board game contains 10 Totoro related figurines, big camphor three, tokens and many cards with beautiful drawings from original movie.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
